name: Colphene Uni NG Tieback Slab L4 (ITC)
Details
Substrate - To Pile Base
All surfaces dry, clean, smooth and free from sharp objects, laitance, oils, grease or any foreign materials which may inhibit or reduce adhesion.
Commencement of installation shall be taken as acceptance of the substrate by the Applicator
Colphene BSW UNI NG - To Pile Base
Confirm rolls stored upright, with the selvedge side on top. If the product is stored outdoors confirm covered with an protective cover
Check COLPHENE BSW UNI NG thickness is 4mm
Apply COLPHENE BSW UNI NG loose laid on blinding concrete
Confirm minimum 100 mm side overlap
Confirm minimum 150 mm end lap between each strip
Confirm end laps are staggered by at least 300 mm
Confirm laps avoid excessive layering
Visual inspection of joint welds at cross laps
Confirm no laps at capping beam construction joint
Confirm all side laps are sealed and end laps by heat-welding the selvedge with a propane torch and minimum 3-8mm bleed
Confirm all angle changes (inside and outside corners) are reinforced by heat-welding on additional 300 mm piece of COLPHENE BSW UNI NG centered on the angle
Alsan EP M - To Pile Base
MIXING - The mix ratio is 1:1 by volume, 1 parts Part A and 1 part Part B. Care should be taken to ensure that ALSAN EP M is thoroughly mixed.
The entire contents of the hardener (Part B) tin should be poured into the base (Part A) tin and the two materials thoroughly mixed using a suitable slow-speed drill and high shear mixing paddle

Mix for 2 minutes until a fully uniform grey colour is obtained; the sides of the tins should be scraped, mixing should continue for a further 2 minutes. DO NOT OVER MIX AS THIS MAY INCORPORATE AIR BUBBLES

To facilitate mixing and application at temperatures below 10˚C, the separate components should be warmed in hot water bath or conditions to room temperature, up to a maximum temperature of 25˚C before beginning to mix. If heated to 25˚C, the subsequently mixed material will have a pot life that will be reduced to 45 minutes.
Application - brush/trowel 40mm cove, covering joint from horizontal COLPHENE BSW UNI NG to pile
Cure time @ 25˚C - 12 hours
Store Aslan EP M in chemical bunds provided by Delta
Alsan Flashing & Alsan Fleece - To Pile Base
Mix well the product before use
ALSAN FLASHING is applied with a with a trowel, a brush or a roller in two (2) layers. Each layer must have a minimum wet film thickness of 0.8mm
First layer must be thick enough to completely immerse the reinforcement. POLYFLEECE will be immediately covered with a second layer of ALSAN FLASHING until saturation
Ready to recoat after 2 hours Dry: 12 hours (remains tacky to touch)
Store Aslan FLASHING in chemical bunds provided by Delta
Colphene BSW UNI NG Reiforcement Strip - To Pile Base
Confirm rolls stored upright, with the selvedge side on top. If the product is stored outdoors confirm covered with an protective cover
Check COLPHENE BSW UNI NG thickness is 4mm
Confirm minimum 100 mm side overlap
Confirm minimum 150 mm end lap between each strip

Confirm all angle changes (inside and outside corners) are reinforced by heat-welding on additional 300 mm piece of COLPHENE BSW UNI NG centered on the angle
Colphene BSW UNI NG - To External Capping Beam Face (Post Pour)
ANTIROCK PRIMER can be applied with a brush or roller on clean, dry substrates free of any residue that may hinder adherence. Shake well before using.
It must be thoroughly dry before applying the waterproofing membrane. Drying time will vary depending on air and surface temperature and humidity.
Confirm rolls stored upright, with the selvedge side on top. If the product is stored outdoors confirm covered with an protective cover
Check COLPHENE BSW UNI NG thickness is 4mm
Confirm minimum 100 mm side overlap
Confirm minimum 150 mm end lap between each strip
Confirm end laps are staggered by at least 300 mm
Confirm laps avoid excessive layering
Visual inspection of joint welds at cross laps
Confirm no laps at capping beam construction joint
Confirm all side laps are sealed and end laps by heat-welding the selvedge with a propane torch and minimum 3-8mm bleed
Confirm all angle changes (inside and outside corners) are reinforced by heat-welding on additional 300 mm piece of COLPHENE BSW UNI NG centered on the angle
Sopradrain 20 - To External Capping Beam Face
The substrate must be firm, even, clean and free from loose materials or any construction debris on the surface.
Install SOPRADRAIN 20 with the geotextile facing the backfill.
Join by simply butting edge to edge and overlapping the geotextile overhang and securing with reinforced canvastape
Terminate SOPRADRAIN 20 by nailing pressure bar at required height
